      "writtenOn": "2020-08-11T03:52:52Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "General: Let\u0027s use consistent verbs for fixture-related operations. For example:\n\n- To call Prepare: prepare the fixture/environment\n- To call Close and Prepare: re-prepare the fixture/environment\n- To call Close: close the fixture/environment\n- To call Adjust: adjust the fixture/environment\n\nThat said, now that the Adjust method has a clear purpose, I think that \"reset\" or something similar is a better method name in place of \"adjust\". IMHO \"adjust\" doesn\u0027t have a meaning to restore the state to original one. https://www.ldoceonline.com/dictionary/adjust\n\nLet\u0027s discuss wording offline later.",
      "revId": "451bbe2a342757ceb2f2e4b8791c3a57a085bc18",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
